<item>
            <title>[SPARK-17521] Error when I use sparkContext.makeRDD(Seq())</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-17521</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when i use sc.makeRDD below&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
    val data3 = sc.makeRDD(Seq())&lt;br/&gt;
    println(data3.partitions.length)&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
I got an error:&lt;br/&gt;
Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Positive number of slices required&lt;br/&gt;
We can fix this bug just modify the last line ,do a check of seq.size&lt;br/&gt;
````&lt;br/&gt;
  def makeRDD&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;T: ClassTag&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;(seq: Seq[(T, Seq&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;String&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;)]): RDD&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;T&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; = withScope &lt;/p&gt;
{
    assertNotStopped()
    val indexToPrefs = seq.zipWithIndex.map(t =&amp;gt; (t._2, t._1._2)).toMap
    new ParallelCollectionRDD[T](this, seq.map(_._1), seq.size, indexToPrefs)
  }
&lt;p&gt;```&lt;/p&gt;</description>
